    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>
To find the reciprocal of <m>{2.812}</m> (which is <m>\frac{1}{2.812}</m>) using a mathematical table, follow the steps below.
</p>

<p>
1. In the table of reciprocals, move down the column labelled <m>x</m> until you locate the row <alert><m>{2.8}</m></alert>.
</p>

<p>
2. From this row, move across to the main column headed <alert><m>{1}</m></alert>.
</p>

<p>
3. Read the number at the intersection of this row and column.<br/>
This value is <alert><m>{0.3559}</m></alert>.
</p>

<p>
4. Next, move further along the same row to the <alert>"SUBTRACT"</alert> column (Mean Difference) headed <alert><m>{2}</m></alert>.<br/>
The number you find here is the mean difference, which is <alert><m>{3}</m></alert> (in the last decimal places).
</p>

<p>
5. <alert>Subtract</alert> this mean difference from your first value.<br/>
(Note: We subtract because the reciprocal function <m>\frac{1}{x}</m> decreases as <m>x</m> increases).
</p>

<p>
<me> {0.3559} - 0.000{3} = {0.3556} </me>
</p>

<p>
Therefore, using the table of reciprocals, the reciprocal of <m>{2.812}</m> is <alert><m>{0.3556}</m></alert>.
</p></div></solution>
